TRIMOUNT DREDGING COMPANY, as Owner of THE Motor Tug MELROSE, Appellee, v. THE M/S CLEVELANDER, General Motorship Corporation, Appellant. No. 409. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 7, 1934. Howard W. Ameli, U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y. (Charles E. Wythe, Sp. Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Maurice Gerrisk, of Boston, Mass., and Emery & Pyne, of New York City (Warner Pyne, of New York City, of counsel), for ap-pellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
